<item>
            <title>[LU-15786] fix all_mds_up() defect: get maxage param on mds1 properly</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15786</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The correct maxage parameters on mds1:&lt;br/&gt;
  osp.${FSNAME}-MDT000&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1-N&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;-osp-MDT0000.maxage&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To reproduce the failure just run the following on&lt;br/&gt;
failover setup where mds1_HOST != mds1failover_HOST:&lt;br/&gt;
  sh llmount.sh&lt;br/&gt;
  ONLY=&quot;100b 100c&quot; sh replay-single.sh&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  error: get_param: param_path&lt;br/&gt;
   &apos;osp/*MDT0000*MDT0001/maxage&apos;: No such file or directory&lt;br/&gt;
  sleep: missing operand&lt;br/&gt;
  Try &apos;sleep --help&apos; for more information.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixes: 436cd4fd21 (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14938&quot; title=&quot;fail_abort() in t-f should take care of MDTs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-14938&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-14938&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; tests: fail_abort() in t-f to take care of MDTs&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
